<subSubSection pageNumber="13" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:245575" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lachnomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Lachnomyrmex amazonicus Feitosa &amp; Brandão" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonicus">Lachnomyrmex amazonicus</taxonomicName>
is known from Amazonian Brazil, in 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.6" unit="m" value="130.0" valueMax="200.0" valueMin="60.0">60-200m</quantity>
elevation rainforest. It is one of the few species in the genus occurring in lowland forests rather than in submontane localities. All records refer to workers obtained in samples of sifted litter from the forest floor.
</paragraph>
